### Test Authentication API

### 1. Sign Up
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 2. Sign In
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/signin
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 3. Get Profile (Replace ACCESS_TOKEN with actual token from signup/signin)
GET http://localhost:3000/auth/profile
Authorization: Bearer ACCESS_TOKEN

### 4. Refresh Token (Replace REFRESH_TOKEN with actual token)
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "REFRESH_TOKEN"
}

### 5. Get All Users (Replace ACCESS_TOKEN with actual token)
GET http://localhost:3000/users
Authorization: Bearer ACCESS_TOKEN

### 6. Logout (Replace REFRESH_TOKEN with actual token)
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/logout
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "REFRESH_TOKEN"
}

### 7. Test Invalid Login
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/signin
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "wrong@example.com",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

### 8. Test Duplicate Signup
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Another User",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 9. Verify Email (Replace with actual code from email)
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/verify-email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "code": "123456"
}

### 10. Resend Verification Code
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/resend-verification
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com"
}

### 11. Resend Verification Code for Already Verified User
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/resend-verification
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "verified@example.com"
}

